WEBVTT

00:00.938 --> 00:02.489
<i>Previously on:</i>

00:02.705 --> 00:08.242
Zoey, will you do me the honor
of becoming Zoey Hyde...

00:08.244 --> 00:11.962
Tottingham-Pierce-Schmidt?

00:11.964 --> 00:14.515
No, I'm sorry!
I can't do it!

00:17.769 --> 00:19.353
I need an answer.

00:19.355 --> 00:20.888
There's someone else.

00:22.256 --> 00:24.491
Look, I'm just gonna be
alone for a while.

00:24.493 --> 00:27.094
And if the real thing
comes along, I'll know it.

00:27.096 --> 00:29.146
Excuse me.

00:29.148 --> 00:31.949
Can I have
your nuts?

00:31.951 --> 00:33.200
This girl's really interesting.

00:33.202 --> 00:35.953
Actually, I think you know her.
Her name's Rose.

00:35.955 --> 00:37.604
See ya!

00:38.657 --> 00:40.107
She's devious and deceptive!

00:40.109 --> 00:42.459
She's probably listening to us
right now!

00:42.461 --> 00:44.962
Hey, Rose,
how ya doing?!

00:44.964 --> 00:47.798
I told Alan that we met.
Boy, did you call that one.

00:47.800 --> 00:49.833
Let me guess.
At some point did he say,

00:49.835 --> 00:51.618
"She's probably listening to us
right now"?

00:51.620 --> 00:54.788
"Hey, Rose, how ya doing?!"

00:54.790 --> 00:57.024
He is very suspicious of you.

00:57.026 --> 00:58.375
Are you suspicious of me?

00:58.377 --> 01:00.260
More curious than suspicious.

01:00.262 --> 01:01.045
Good.

01:01.047 --> 01:03.047
So, what do you say? Dinner?

01:03.049 --> 01:04.548
To dinner.

01:04.550 --> 01:07.434
It'll be nice to go out with
someone normal for a change.

01:10.455 --> 01:12.406
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

01:17.196 --> 01:18.896
Yay!

01:18.898 --> 01:21.949
Yay, indeed.

01:21.951 --> 01:25.869
Ooh, we went a mile
and a half.

01:25.871 --> 01:27.554
What is that,
a pedometer?

01:27.556 --> 01:30.124
Yes, I'm measuring
our sex life,

01:30.126 --> 01:33.594
and as of today, we are
in Laughlin, Nevada.

01:33.596 --> 01:35.829
Well, I believe I did most
of the driving.

01:35.831 --> 01:37.681
Yes. But when you got
a flat,

01:37.683 --> 01:39.566
I stopped and
pumped it up.

01:44.140 --> 01:49.176
Call me crazy-- and the State of
California did for a while--

01:49.178 --> 01:52.179
but these last couple of weeks
have been the best of my life.

01:52.181 --> 01:54.782
They have been great.

01:54.784 --> 01:57.484
With the last mile and a half
being a particular high point.

01:57.486 --> 01:59.319
That's because
you finally stopped

01:59.321 --> 02:01.071
and asked for directions.

02:04.659 --> 02:06.910
Okay, I better get going.

02:06.912 --> 02:09.863
No, no.
Stay the night.

02:09.865 --> 02:11.665
All my stuff is
at my house, silly.

02:11.667 --> 02:12.800
What stuff?

02:12.802 --> 02:14.451
I don't know.
My toothbrush.

02:14.453 --> 02:15.702
You can use mine.

02:15.704 --> 02:17.838
Ugh!

02:17.840 --> 02:19.723
After what we just did,
you're really concerned

02:19.725 --> 02:21.541
with having my toothbrush
in your mouth?

02:24.045 --> 02:27.481
I'm just saying, at some point
I have to go home.

02:27.483 --> 02:32.653
What if you never
had to go home?

02:32.655 --> 02:35.722
Do you mean like you're
gonna tie me up

02:35.724 --> 02:37.574
and keep me bound
and gagged in the closet?

02:37.576 --> 02:44.131
Uh, no. I was thinking more
like you move in with me.

02:44.133 --> 02:47.835
Hmm, that's a little odd.

02:47.837 --> 02:49.953
I mean, come on.
You said so yourself,

02:49.955 --> 02:51.672
the last few weeks
have been fantastic.

02:51.674 --> 02:53.240
We get along great.
Why not?

02:53.242 --> 02:55.793
Why not?

02:55.795 --> 02:58.411
Because I don't want to be
a flavorless cracker.

02:58.413 --> 03:00.597
Sure.

03:00.599 --> 03:01.965
What?

03:03.885 --> 03:06.887
Well, you know when you order
a cheese plate

03:06.889 --> 03:09.223
and you get two different
kinds of stinky cheese

03:09.225 --> 03:13.393
and then you eat that little,
bland, unsalted cracker

03:13.395 --> 03:14.778
in between to cleanse
your palate?

03:14.780 --> 03:19.633
Not really, but you
explained it pretty well.

03:19.635 --> 03:23.570
Well, I don't want to be
the bland cracker.

03:23.572 --> 03:25.939
I want to be
the stinky cheese.

03:25.941 --> 03:27.958
Okay, I think I understand.

03:27.960 --> 03:30.127
You're concerned 'cause
I just got out

03:30.129 --> 03:31.712
of a serious relationship,

03:31.714 --> 03:34.164
and you don't want to be
the girl that gets me

03:34.166 --> 03:35.282
to the next one.

03:35.284 --> 03:36.667
Exactly.

03:36.669 --> 03:39.386
Well, trust me.

03:39.388 --> 03:43.173
You are the stinkies.

03:44.792 --> 03:46.459
So sweet.

03:46.461 --> 03:49.313
I don't know,
it's moving so quickly.

03:49.315 --> 03:53.484
I mean, who could've seen
this coming?

03:53.486 --> 03:57.137
Now, I know it's moving quick,
but I'm the kind of person

03:57.139 --> 04:00.941
when I see something I want,
I stop at nothing to get it.

04:00.943 --> 04:04.995
Wow, I guess opposites
really do attract.

04:07.982 --> 04:12.753
Just promise me that
you'll think about it.

04:12.755 --> 04:16.740
And you'll think about
tying me up in your closet?

04:16.742 --> 04:18.058
I will.

04:18.060 --> 04:20.827
That seems fair.

04:23.298 --> 04:25.516
You know, if we get
started now, we can make it

04:25.518 --> 04:27.467
to Salt Lake City by daybreak.

04:27.469 --> 04:32.055
Okay, but this time I'm driving.

